2020-04-02
Summary: 
Amazon (AMZN) is facing increased scrutiny due to its handling of the COVID-19 pandemic. The company has banned the sale of N95 and surgical masks to the general public, and will roll out temperature checks and face masks for staff at all its U.S. and European warehouses and Whole Foods. Amazon has also filled 80,000 jobs in the span of a few weeks, part of a hiring spree to add 100,000 workers to meet soaring demand. However, lawmakers and unions are putting pressure on the company over its handling of the pandemic.
